name: Koki Restaurant Nusa Dua
address: Jl. Siligita No.101x, Nusa Dua, Kec. Kuta Sel., Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80361, Indonesia
review 1: Im korean food lover especially for jeyuk bokkeum and sundubu jiggae. Both taste fantastic here. I would love it more if it's spicy and thinner, slice of pork belly. Kimchi is marinated long enough. Most other places serve kimchi haven't marinated yet. I would definitely come back here when i come to bali.
review 2: I ordered the cold noodles and mandu. Both are great. The broth in the cold noodles is very deep yet fresh. The mandu has a lot of filling and thin skin, which I like. I arrived around 3pm, so the place was not crowded. The service was fast.
review 3: I ordered grilled pork belly, cold noodles, and bibimbap, and the amount was large and the taste was good. It would be good to come here once in a while when you want to eat real Korean food. And the vitamin juice was super good.
review 4: It is autentic korean rest which the owner is korean. Try it especially when you are boring with bali local food. Bon appeti ü•¢
review 5: The taste of the dish is elevating the palate, very delicious. And the owner were very kind and greet us while dining. Great experience.

name: HARBOUR ONE RESTURANT
address: Jln Bypass nusa dua, Bypass Jl. Tol Bali Mandara, Benoa, Kec. Kuta Sel., Kabupaten Badung, Bali, Indonesia
review 1: The price is absolutely horrific, even more expensive than Sydney I would say. Food is decent. Would much recommend Sentosa Seafood in Kuta instead if you‚Äôre looking for something similar (spent $200  at Sentosa and ate much more too compared to here where we paid $450 and didn‚Äôt eat very much).
review 2:
All food is amazing! i love the pecking duck, shrimps, and the shark lip . The service is kind and fast.
The slight drawback is that the AC in the room is not cold
review 3: Bad services, when we come in there is very few people but the restaurant still take lots of time to come out and give other people that come in after us (who are mostly chinese). Not recommending, very bad attitude and will never come back.
review 4: I would avoid this place for several reasons. They allow smoking inside without any dedicated section. They overcharged the drinks by not showing the menu. You would be surprised how much they charged for a regular hot drink. Finally they give small portion for meats. They are generous with white rice however. Their service is subpar overall. review 5: This is a typical Chinese restaurant. Single storey big restaurant at Nusa Dua. Most patrons are businessman so the prices are pretty steep and expensive . The foods served are average sized and quite tasty.

name: A&B Homestay and Kitchen
address: Gg. Bambu No.8D, Benoa, Kec. Kuta Sel., Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80361, Indonesia
review 1: Lovely family run Homestay. They were quick to respond when trying to reserve the room. They allowed me to look at one of the rooms before booking. It is a spacious basic room, clean, good WiFi. Bathroom is a wet room, and no hot water (which is welcomed in Bali) they had soap and shampoo and towels. The room is just as seen in pictures. It was a great rate of 175.000/night and had everything we needed. I definitely recommend this Homestay.
review 2: This homestay was so lovely. The owner is very very friendly, they let me to use the kitchen everyday and they always offers me a lot of stuff to use or to eat from the kitchen. Once we got invited to the party with their family and we eat together. I feel like not staying in a homestay, but feels like staying with my family ‚ù§Ô∏èü•∞ This hotel is very recommended to stay and very close to the best beach at Nusa Nua plus the immigration office
review 3:
Very nice place, great family. I felt like I was home, they treated us like a family member. The room is clean, you can have access to the kitchen. A lot of warungs and laundry service next to the house. It‚Äôs a good value for money.
We booked for 2 days and we ended up staying 3 weeks.
Thank you.
review 4:
The price is very nice!
Good condition for all
Have scooters parking
Nice owner
Everything is good, enjoy here
review 5: Lovely place! Clean and big rooms. Very nice owner and super flexible, we extend our staay a couple of times. You can use the kitchen. It has a lot of warungs close by, as well as a food court in case you want more international food. Easy access with scooter to the beach. Safe area!

address: Jl. Pintas Siligita Selatan, Benoa, Kec. Kuta Sel., Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80361, Indonesia
review 1:
Soto dobrak is a cute hip Indonesian restaurant serving soto, nasi goreng and mie goreng  and also a vegetarian favorite: Gado-gado.
It ultra clean and modern and has a nice feel about it.
The breaded shrimp either part of a meal or added as a 6000rp side are tasty and almost a cross between a donut and a breaded shrimp...recomended to try.
review 2:
My First time and their Soto is definitely their specialty. Perfect punch of herbs, spices, and chicken stock presents a great flavor of Javanese style Soto. Had  tried their newest ‚ÄúAyam Geprek‚Äù and it‚Äôs still need improvement. Affordable food, clean place and friendly staff. Unfortunately, there is only side-road parking for your vehicles.
WARNING: if you have trouble or are easily annoyed with loud noise, simply tell the staff. A loud bang is their signature bell for the Soto
review 3: Good food, quick service, clean place, low prices. Reccomended
review 4: Good taste, and a (very) cheap price, but the place is so small.

name: Nasi Padang Nusadua Minang
address: Jl. Bypass Ngurah Rai No.16, Benoa, Kec. Kuta Sel., Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80361, Indonesia
review 1:
I recently had the pleasure of ordering Nasi Padang Nusadua Minang through Gojek, and I was very impressed with the food and the service.

The beef rendang was absolutely delicious. It was tender and flavorful, with a rich and complex sauce. The rice was perfectly cooked, and the other side dishes were also very good.

I was also impressed with the speed of the delivery. My order arrived within 30 minutes, which is very impressive for a restaurant in Nusa Dua.

Overall, I had a very positive experience with Nasi Padang Nusadua Minang. The food was delicious and halal, the service was excellent, and the delivery was fast. I would definitely recommend this restaurant to anyone looking for a delicious and authentic Indonesian meal.

My only issue is more beef would be appreciated and sometimes can be tough to chew.
review 2: Delicious nasi padang in Nusa Dua. It was still opens in midnight. So very helpful during my late flight arrival. The staff were friendly and professional. The price was also friendly :)
review 3: Best nasi padang in Nusa Dua. Tasty food excellent service. Went for multiple servings as it was too delicious. Price was relatively cheap. Will come back and visit again.
review 4: The worst nasi padang i‚Äôve ever try, the rice is so wet, i‚Äôd rather to say it porridge. The waitress just did a scam to me, which the food didn‚Äôt come as my order. The waitress also denial when i did complaining, such a bad idea to get your food here
review 5: One of the best masakang padang I've ever had in Bali. They cook the rice with coconut milk and everything is so yummy!! The place is clean and staff speaks english. Enak sekali  :)

review 1:
Absolutely the best choice to try when craving for Kambing. They even have Sate Buntel menu with such an affordable price and surely yummiest in the island.

The Ibu is so humble and greets everyone with her big smiles. Try the Sate Kambing, Sate Buntel, Tongseng & Nasgor Kambing!

Parking is streetsidea and the seating capacity is limited, better to take out if you order larger portions.
review 2: For those who are tired of madura peanut sauce in Bali, this place is the best choice. Authentic taste. Finally found Solo OG. Sate buntel, krengsengan, and tengkleng are mandatory. You can modify anything, the owners are so friendly.
review 3:
I love Tongseng Buntel.

review 4: Their mutton dish are masterpieces.. especially my favorite, krengseng.. eventhough its a bit pricey, but for your culinary experiece sake, it is a must try.
review 5: If you are looking for Solo style lamb satay in Bali then this is a place to go.. the satay is very soft.. other than satay, you could try other recipes like tengkreng, gulai etc
